					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Minhagim relating to the ritual for the fasts and festivals as used in Germany.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="77v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Minhagim</title>
							<title n="0" xml:lang="he">מנהגים</title>
							<note>
								<p>The writer distinguishes between the minhag of most of Ashkenaz and its local derivations (see e.g. folio 13v, 19v). There are references to Minhagim of Mahari"l (e.g. 42r, 16r, 26r).</p>
								<p>The table of contents (folios 75v-77r) is imperfect at the end.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלמו זה המנהגים בחודש <date calendar="Hebrew">כט תמוז שיד</date> במזל טוב אמן.<locus n="75r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>77 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>185</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
